title: Part C
stimulusHtml:
Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples to score the response.

A response with no separation of variables earns 0 out of 4 points.

A response of − 1 6 ∫ 1 S−36   dS = ∫  dt MathType@MTEF@5@5@+= feaagKart1ev2aaatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLn hiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr 4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk 0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr 0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaaqaaaaaaaaaWdbi abgkHiTmaalaaabaGaaGymaaqaaiaaiAdaaaWaa8qGbeqaamaalaaa baGaaGymaaqaaiaadofacqGHsislcaaIZaGaaGOnaaaacaaMc8UaaG PaVlaadsgacaWGtbaaleqabeqdcaGLRicakiabg2da9maapeyabeaa caaMc8UaamizaiaadshaaSqabeqaniaawUIiaaaa@4C24@ is a bad separation and does not earn the first point. However, this response is eligible for the second and third points. It cannot earn the fourth point.

A response that enters with both correct antiderivatives earns the first 2 points.

If the absolute value is missing on the antiderivative of 1 S−36 MathType@MTEF@5@5@+= feaagKart1ev2aaatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLn hiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr 4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk 0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr 0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaaqaaaaaaaaaWdbm aalaaabaGaaGymaaqaaiaadofacqGHsislcaaIZaGaaGOnaaaaaaa@3D2A@ the response earns the second point and is eligible for the third point. The response is not eligible for the fourth point.

A response with no constant of integration can earn at most the first 2 points.

A response is eligible for the third point if it has earned the first point and has at least one of the two antiderivatives correct. A response earns the third point by correctly including the constant of integration in an equation involving the presented antiderivatives and then replacing t with 0 and S with 0. This point is earned even in the presence of nonreal values (e.g., ln( −36 ) MathType@MTEF@5@5@+= feaagKart1ev2aqatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLn hiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr 4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk 0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr 0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaaciGGSbGaaiOBam aabmaabaGaeyOeI0IaaG4maiaaiAdaaiaawIcacaGLPaaaaaa@3ED5@ ) or severe algebraic errors.

A response is eligible for the fourth point only if it has earned the first 3 points and has correctly handled absolute value in all steps.
